author: kfogel
msg: Fix bug reported by Sander Striker.  This fix improves error handling
in mod_dav_svn, by not sending the closing tag for an update if the
open tag wasn't sent.  But it reveals a much nastier bug, which is
described in more detail in a comment in the new regression test
below.
* subversion/mod_dav_svn/update.c
(update_ctx_t): New flag field `started_update'.
(upd_set_target_revision): Set the new flag.
(dav_svn__update_report): Check the flag before closing the update.
* subversion/tests/clients/cmdline/merge_tests.py
(merge_one_file): New XFail test.
(test_list): Run it.
Since subversion.tigris.org is down at the moment, there are no issue
numbers for any of this yet.  Sander's original email was:
From: "Sander Striker" <striker@apache.org>
Subject: Buglet in svn merge?
To: <dev@subversion.tigris.org>
